  "name": "James Ruskin",
  "profile": "Croydon-born (1972) and -based techno producer and DJ. James Ruskin comes from a background that first put him in touch with hip hop and electro, and later with the emerging Detroit techno scenes. This inspired him to become a DJ in 1991 and venture into production with studio partner [a=Richard Polson] by 1994. Founded [l=Blueprint] with Polson in 1996. As Blueprint grew, he delivered his first solo releases and appeared elsewhere as remixer and co-producer.\r\n\r\nHe was also resident DJ at Circulation.",
